Strong white flour
Yeast (it's so much better than bicarb)
Water
Salt
Herbs to taste (rosemary, thyme, oregano)

Your dough will need a 5:3 ratio of flour to water, so measure out as much as 
you want
Put the dry ingredients (except the yeast!) in a mixing bowl and stir
Mix the yeast in with some lukewarm water and let it activate a bit (bubbles)
Add the liquid slowly to the dry ingredients. Stop if the mixture looks like
it's getting too wet
Knead the doughball well, you want to stretch that gluten out as much as poss
Let the dough rise in a warm room, until double in size
Punch the air out of the dough and then put it in the oven
oven: 230C 30 minutes
